snippet: A previous agreement was dropped last month by the European Parliament over concerns of overfishing and other issues.
abstract: Maria Damanaki, European commissioner for maritime affairs and fisheries, pledges to work for a new fishing treaty with Morocco after previous agreement was dropped by the European Parliament over concerns of overfishing and other issues.
lead_paragraph: A previous agreement was dropped last month by the European Parliament over concerns of overfishing and other issues.
